'''CONEXPO-CON/AGG''' is a [[trade show]] for the construction industry that takes place every three years. CONEXPO-CON/AGG is a result of the merger of CONEXPO and CON/AGG in 1996.<ref>{{cite book | last = Haycraft | first = William R. | title = Yellow Steel: The Story of the Earthmoving Equipment Industry | pages = 366-367 | publisher = University of Illinois Press | year = 2002 | isbn = 0-2520-7104-2}}</ref> It is held at the [[Las Vegas Convention Center]] with the next show held March 10-14, 2020. The [[International Exposition for Power Transmission]] (IFPE) is held in conjunction with Conexpo-Con/Agg.<ref name=cc>{{cite web |url=http://www.conexpoconagg.com |title=Conexpo-Con/Agg 2014 - The Trade show for construction and construction materials |accessdate=2011-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last = Miskelly | first = Matthew | title = Trade Shows Worldwide | page = 1557 | publisher = Cengage Gale | year = 2006 | isbn = 0-7876-8968-8}}</ref>
== History == In 1909, the first CONEXPO was held in Columbus, Ohio, and the first CON/AGG was held in Detroit Michigan in 1928. In 1994 the two show merged, creating CONEXPO-CON/AGG. The first joint show was held in 1996 in Las Vegas, Nevada. CONEXPO-CON/AGG has gone on to become the western hemisphere's largest show for the construction and construction materials industries. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.exhibitcitynews.com/glimpse-tradeshow-history-5/|title=A glimpse of tradeshow history {{!}} Exhibit City News|website=www.exhibitcitynews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-04-25}}</ref>
The world’s first 3D-printed excavator and the new Tech Experience debuted at the 2017.show.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tsnn.com/news-blogs/conexpoconagg-and-ifpe-break-records-las-vegas-28-mil-net-sq-ft|title=CONEXPO-CON/AGG and IFPE Break Records in Las Vegas with 2.8+ Mil Net Sq. Ft. {{!}} TSNN Trade Show News|website=www.tsnn.com|language=en|access-date=2017-04-26}}</ref>
